(5, 'Enable Cookies', 'one_column', NULL, NULL, 'enable-cookies', NULL, '<div class="std">\n    <ul class="messages">\n        <li class="notice-msg">\n            <ul>\n                <li>Please enable cookies in your web browser to continue.</li>\n            </ul>\n        </li>\n    </ul>\n    <div class="page-title">\n        <h1><a name="top"></a>What are Cookies?</h1>\n    </div>\n    <p>Cookies are short pieces of data that are sent to your computer when you visit a website.\n    On later visits, this data is then returned to that website. Cookies allow us to recognize you automatically\n    whenever you visit our site so that we can personalize your experience and provide you with better service.\n    We also use cookies (and similar browser data, such as Flash cookies) for fraud prevention and other purposes.\n     If your web browser is set to refuse cookies from our website, you will not be able to complete a purchase\n     or take advantage of certain features of our website, such as storing items in your Shopping Cart or\n     receiving personalized recommendations. As a result, we strongly encourage you to configure your web\n     browser to accept cookies from our website.</p>\n    <h2 class="subtitle">Enabling Cookies</h2>\n    <ul class="disc">\n        <li><a href="#ie7">Internet Explorer 7.x</a></li>\n        <li><a href="#ie6">Internet Explorer 6.x</a></li>\n        <li><a href="#firefox">Mozilla/Firefox</a></li>\n        <li><a href="#opera">Opera 7.x</a></li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3><a name="ie7"></a>Internet Explorer 7.x</h3>\n    <ol>\n        <li>\n            <p>Start Internet Explorer</p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>Under the <strong>Tools</strong> menu, click <strong>Internet Options</strong></p>\n            <p><img src="{{skin url="images/cookies/ie7-1.gif"}}" alt="" /></p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>Click the <strong>Privacy</strong> tab</p>\n            <p><img src="{{skin url="images/cookies/ie7-2.gif"}}" alt="" /></p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>Click the <strong>Advanced</strong> button</p>\n            <p><img src="{{skin url="images/cookies/ie7-3.gif"}}" alt="" /></p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>Put a check mark in the box for <strong>Override Automatic Cookie Handling</strong>,\n            put another check mark in the <strong>Always accept session cookies </strong>box</p>\n            <p><img src="{{skin url="images/cookies/ie7-4.gif"}}" alt="" /></p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>Click <strong>OK</strong></p>\n            <p><img src="{{skin url="images/cookies/ie7-5.gif"}}" alt="" /></p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>Click <strong>OK</strong></p>\n            <p><img src="{{skin url="images/cookies/ie7-6.gif"}}" alt="" /></p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>Restart Internet Explore</p>\n        </li>\n    </ol>\n    <p class="a-top"><a href="#top">Back to Top</a></p>\n    <h3><a name="ie6"></a>Internet Explorer 6.x</h3>\n    <ol>\n        <li>\n            <p>Select <strong>Internet Options</strong> from the Tools menu</p>\n            <p><img src="{{skin url="images/cookies/ie6-1.gif"}}" alt="" /></p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>Click on the <strong>Privacy</strong> tab</p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>Click the <strong>Default</strong> button (or manually slide the bar down to <strong>Medium</strong>)\n            under <strong>Settings</strong>. Click <strong>OK</strong></p>\n            <p><img src="{{skin url="images/cookies/ie6-2.gif"}}" alt="" /></p>\n        </li>\n    </ol>\n    <p class="a-top"><a href="#top">Back to Top</a></p>\n    <h3><a name="firefox"></a>Mozilla/Firefox</h3>\n    <ol>\n        <li>\n            <p>Click on the <strong>Tools</strong>-menu in Mozilla</p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>Click on the <strong>Options...</strong> item in the menu - a new window open</p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>Click on the <strong>Privacy</strong> selection in the left part of the window. (See image below)</p>\n            <p><img src="{{skin url="images/cookies/firefox.png"}}" alt="" /></p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>Expand the <strong>Cookies</strong> section</p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>Check the <strong>Enable cookies</strong> and <strong>Accept cookies normally</strong> checkboxes</p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>Save changes by clicking <strong>Ok</strong>.</p>\n        </li>\n    </ol>\n    <p class="a-top"><a href="#top">Back to Top</a></p>\n    <h3><a name="opera"></a>Opera 7.x</h3>\n    <ol>\n        <li>\n            <p>Click on the <strong>Tools</strong> menu in Opera</p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>Click on the <strong>Preferences...</strong> item in the menu - a new window open</p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>Click on the <strong>Privacy</strong> selection near the bottom left of the window. (See image below)</p>\n            <p><img src="{{skin url="images/cookies/opera.png"}}" alt="" /></p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>The <strong>Enable cookies</strong> checkbox must be checked, and <strong>Accept all cookies</strong>\n            should be selected in the &quot;<strong>Normal cookies</strong>&quot; drop-down</p>\n        </li>\n        <li>\n            <p>Save changes by clicking <strong>Ok</strong></p>\n        </li>\n    </ol>\n    <p class="a-top"><a href="#top">Back to Top</a></p>\n</div>\n', '2016-02-22 13:24:55', '2016-02-22 13:24:55', 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(6, 'Privacy', 'one_column', NULL, NULL, 'privacy', NULL, '<header class="entry-header">\r\n<h1 class="entry-title">PRIVACY</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n<div class="entry-content">\r\n<div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid">\r\n<div class="row-container">\r\n<div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12">\r\n<div class="wpb_wrapper">\r\n<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">\r\n<div class="wpb_wrapper">\r\n<p class="justify">RENT-A-BAG respects your concerns about privacy and follows strict procedures to protect customer information and ensures that your personal information is handled in a responsible manner. We do not disclose information you provide to third parties.<br />Currently, RENT-A-BAG gathers online customer information to enhance your online experience with us, to improve and maintain the content of our website, and for marketing and promotional purposes.<br />We collect information from you when you complete our feedback or contact form and additionally, when you hire products from our online shop. We may use this information to advise you of changes to our website, or to let you know about our newest products. We may also record which products you are interested in or enquire after so as to improve our features and customer service on our website.<br />Postal addresses and telephone numbers are used for processing orders, delivering merchandise, obtaining information and when communication is needed directly relating to orders or enquiries placed through our site.<br />Addresses may also be used for periodic mailings from RENT-A-BAG about new products and services. Cookies are used in our on-line store, but only to keep track of the contents of your shopping cart once you have selected an item.<br />If you do not wish to receive e-mail about our newest products, please advise us by telephone on +44 (0) 20 3290 9498 or by e-mail at info@rent-a-bag.club.</p>\r\n<h3>OVERVIEW</h3>\r\n<p class="justify">RENT-A-BAG acknowledges the importance of protecting your personal information. Therefore, we have developed security measures to protect your data.<br />RENT-A-BAG&rsquo;s website was designed for minimal use of your personal data. We do not reveal your identity when it can be accomplished anonymously.<br />Each time that you use the Services, you agree to be bound by the Terms and Conditions and this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree to these terms, you should not browse this website.<br />RENT-A-BAG controls and determines the purposes by which your personal information is used and shared, including all security measures.<br />RENT-A-BAG ensures that personal information is processed in strict compliance with the Great British and where applicable European law.<br />Our Privacy Policy provides all the information you need to know about our privacy practices. However, if you have any doubts about this Privacy Policy, you can learn more by writing an email to info@rent-a-bag.club.</p>\r\n<h3>DATA WE KEEP AND HOW WE USE IT</h3>\r\n<p class="justify">RENT-A-BAG reserves the right to assign external parties to help process your personal data. These external parties are experienced, trustworthy and operate with the laws and regulations.<br />By completing an online registration, the customer grants RENT-A-BAG their consent to use their personal information and address, as well as any information concerning their methods of payment. These information will be stored and processed by computer and may be used for communication purposes or to process orders.<br />You will be the only person hold responsible for the illegal use and disclosure of this information by third parties.<br />The personal information we ask you to provide, such as email address, home address, card number and others, are necessary to process and fulfil your order, give effect to obligations of applicable laws and regulations or to provide other services requested by you. If you refuse to provide us with certain personal information, you may prevent us from processing your hire process or other services, such as Customer Support, personal Fashion Assistants or others.<br />The disclosure of your personal information beyond what is necessary is optional and does not affect the use of any services of this website. We mark the mandatory information with an asterisk (*).<br />Your personal information may be disclosed to third parties, such as external entities contracted by RENT-A-BAG, or who independently treat personal information collected by RENT-A-BAG.</p>\r\n<h3>PASSIVE DATA COLLECTION</h3>\r\n<p class="justify">RENT-A-BAG may use your personal information for the processing of orders, payments and to provide you with a personalised shopping experience. We will also use your details to fulfil and deliver your orders and manage your account.<br />Any disclosure will not exceed the purpose for which your personal information was collected and processed.</p>\r\n<p>Your personal information may be disclosed to third parties to comply with applicable laws or valid legal processes, respond to judicial inquiries, and protect the rights or property of RENT-A-BAG.</p>\r\n<p>Your personal information will not be disclosed to third parties without prior notice and your consent.<br />We will do our best to avoid any possible risks for customers. RENT-A-BAG has security measures to protect your personal information against destruction, loss, alteration or any other unlawful acts. However, RENT-A-BAG cannot guarantee that the security measures adopted will prevent any risk of unauthorised access or loss of data.</p>\r\n<h3>COOKIES</h3>\r\n<p class="justify">Our site uses cookies (very small files that are sent by us to your computer or other access device) which we can access when you visit our site in future.</p>\r\n<p class="justify">There are four types of cookies:<br />Website functionality cookies: These cookies enable you to browse the website and use our features such as shopping baskets and wish lists.</p>\r\n<p class="justify">Website analytics cookies: We use these cookies to measure and analyse how our customers use the website. This allows us to continuously improve our website and your shopping experience.</p>\r\n<p class="justify">Customer preference cookies: When browsing or shopping online, the website will remember preferences you make (for example your user name, language or location). This makes your browsing experience simpler, easier and more personal to you.</p>\r\n<p class="justify">Targeting cookies or advertising cookies: These cookies are used to deliver adverts relevant to you. In addition, they limit the number of times you see an advertisement as well as helping us measure the effectiveness of our advertising campaigns.</p>\r\n<p class="justify">By using our website you agree that we can place these types of cookies on your device and access them when you visit the site in the future.</p>\r\n<p class="justify">If you want to delete any cookies that are already on your computer, please refer to the help and support area on your internet browser for instructions on how to locate the file or directory that stores cookies.</p>\r\n<p class="justify">Information on deleting or controlling cookies is available at www.AboutCookies.org. Please note that by deleting our cookies or disabling future cookies you may not be able to access certain areas or features of our site.</p>\r\n<h3>OTHER TITLE</h3>\r\n<p class="justify">You have the right to obtain, at any time, a confirmation that your information is being processed and to be informed about the origin of the source and purpose of your data&rsquo;s transmission. Your personal information will not be disclosed to third parties without prior notice.<br />At any time, you have the right to:<br />&ndash; Update, correct or delete your personal information;<br />&ndash; Obtain a prior notice that your information is being processed, except when it is impossible to do so, or if it means overruling the rights which it invokes;<br />&ndash; Object to the processing of your data, for any reasons.<br />You can freely exercise your rights and get more information by writing your doubts to:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@rent-a-bag.club">info@rent-a-bag.club</a>.<br />When you submit content, you grant RENT-A-BAG authorisation to distribute it in the future, without any compensation.<br />RENT-A-BAG may use these same contents on television channel, digital means of communications or others, for any purpose without any compensation.<br />RENT-A-BAG may change these terms, even if applicable laws and regulations do not require it. Our customers will be informed of any changes or updates to this website. All changes and updates will be implemented once they have been published in this website.<br />For the most up to date version of our Privacy Policy, you should regularly access these terms.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '2016-02-22 13:24:55', '2016-03-18 12:39:11', 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7, 'About us', 'two_columns_right', NULL, NULL, 'about-us', NULL, '<header class="entry-header">\r\n<h1 class="entry-title">ABOUT US</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n<div class="entry-content">\r\n<div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid">\r\n<div class="row-container">\r\n<div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12">\r\n<div class="wpb_wrapper">\r\n<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">\r\n<div class="wpb_wrapper">\r\n<p class="abt">We are a company of LUXURIOUS HANDBAGS.&nbsp;Apparently there has not been a lady who would not borrow a handbag from a friend. Be it for a special occasion or just to break an existing handbag range girlfriends turn to each other to borrow this luxurious accessory.</p>\r\n<p class="abt">With&nbsp;<span>RENT-A-BAG</span>&nbsp;we are bringing a choice of beautiful handbags to your doorstep skipping an enquiry from the girlfriends.&nbsp;<span>Just with few clicks away you could choose a handbag for rent.</span></p>\r\n<p class="abt">We transform your wardrobe with:</p>\r\n<p class="abt">The most AMAZING HANDPICKED BRANDS&nbsp;and&nbsp;DESIGNS;<br />RIDICULOUSLY EASY&nbsp;steps;<br />IMPECCABLE SERVICE.</p>\r\n<p class="abt">We&nbsp;<span>passionately believe</span>&nbsp;that LOOKING AMAZING&nbsp;<span>should not cost you a fortune</span>. Thus, we also offer you an innovative concept of GETTING ALL YOUR MONEY BACK&nbsp;with a purchase of a handbag from us.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '2016-03-18 12:23:34', '2016-03-18 20:23:17', 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(8, 'Careers', 'two_columns_right', NULL, NULL, 'careers', NULL, '<header class="entry-header">\r\n<h1 class="entry-title">CAREERS</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n<div class="entry-content">\r\n<div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid">\r\n<div class="row-container">\r\n<div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12">\r\n<div class="wpb_wrapper">\r\n<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">\r\n<div class="wpb_wrapper">\r\n<p class="justify">If you are talented, enthusiastic, have passion for luxury fashion industry, e-commerce and if you would like to join our family like team, we would like to hear from you. Please send your CV and covering letter to&nbsp;<a href="mailto:careers@rent-a-bag.club">careers@rent-a-bag.club.</a></p>\r\n<p class="justify">From time to time we also publish job offerings on our careers page. Please be visiting our website to be the first to apply.</p>\r\n<p class="justify">If you are applying for a job with our company, you must be in possession of a valid work permit that allows you to work in the UK on a full time basis.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '2016-03-18 12:27:05', '2016-04-05 13:43:35', 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9, 'FAQ', 'two_columns_right', NULL, NULL, 'faq', NULL, '<header class="entry-header">\r\n<h1 class="entry-title">FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n<div class="entry-content">\r\n<div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid">\r\n<div class="row-container">\r\n<div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12">\r\n<div class="wpb_wrapper">\r\n<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">\r\n<div class="wpb_wrapper">\r\n<h3>ABOUT US</h3>\r\n<div class="question show_hide0">WHAT IS&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide1">ARE THE BAGS AUTHENTIC?</div>\r\n<h3>HOW IT WORKS</h3>\r\n<div class="question show_hide2">HOW DOES&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG WORK?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide3">HOW LONG IS THE RENTAL PROCESS?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide4">ARE THE HANDBAGS I RENT NEW?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide5">HOW FAR IN ADVANCE SHOULD I RESERVE A HANDBAG?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide6">I LIVE OUTSIDE&nbsp;UK AND I WOULD LIKE TO RESERVE A HANDBAG FOR SHIPMENT TO ANOTHER EUROPEAN COUNTRY. IS IT POSSIBLE?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide7">WHAT HAPPENED ONCE THE RENTAL PERIOD OF THE HANDBAG HAS ENDED?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide8">WHAT IF THE HANDBAG DOES NOT MEET MY EXPECTATIONS?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide9">I REMOVED A&nbsp;SWING TAG FROM THE HANDBAG. CAN I ASK FOR THE REFUND?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide10">DO I NEED TO GET AN INSURANCE&nbsp;WHEN I RENT A HANDBAG?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide11">I HAVE AN EVENT TO GO TO WITHIN 24 HOURS. DO I HAVE ENOUGH TIME TO RENT A HANDBAG?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide12">CAN I BORROW MORE THAN ONE BAG AT THE SAME TIME?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide13">HOW DOES&nbsp;BUY TO RENT A BAG WORK?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide14">HOW LONG DO I LOCK MY MONEY FOR BUT TO RENT PURCHASE?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide15">AM I EARNING ANYTHING FROM A&nbsp;BUY&nbsp;TO RENT PURCHASE?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide16">WHAT&rsquo;S IN THEIR FOR ME?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide17">HOW DO I MAKE SURE THAT THE BAG I PURCHASE FOR RENT TO BUY IS A NEW BAG?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide18">HOW DO I GET MY MONEY BACK FROM A&nbsp;BUY TO RENT PURCHASE?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide19">WHAT IF SOMEBODY RETURNS A DIFFERENT BAG, NOT THE ONE WHICH YOU SENT OUT?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide20">WHAT IS THE HANDBAG IN A BAD CONDITION AND I CANNOT USE IT?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide21">WHAT IS THE HANDBAG I PURCHASED FOR BUY-TO-RENT DOES NOT GET RENTED? DO I STILL GET MY MONEY BACK?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide22">WHAT HAPPENS IF THE HANDBAG WHICH I PURCHASED FOR BUY TO RENT GETS LOST, STOLEN OR DAMAGED BEYONG REPAIR?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide23">WHO PAYS FOR DRY-CLEANING OF THE HANDBAGS?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide24">CAN I PURCHASE ANY BAG FOR BUY TO RENT&nbsp;?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide25">I SAW A BAG I WANTED T PUCHASE FOR BUY TO RENT AND COULD NOT PAY FOR IT. WHY?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide26">WHOW TO I KNOW WHEN I AM RECEIVING MY HANDBAG BACK?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide27">I WANT TO MAKE MORE THAN ONE PURCHASE FOR BUY TO RENT. CAN I?</div>\r\n<h3>DELIVERY AND SHIPPING</h3>\r\n<div class="question show_hide28">WHEN WILL MY ORDER ARRIVE?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide29">WHO PAYS FOR THE DELIVERY?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide30">WHERE CAN I FIND MY ORDER NUMBER?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide31">I RESERVED A HANDBAG ONLY 24 HOURS BEFORE THE EVENT. HOW DOES THE PARCEL GET DELIVERED TO ME?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide32">WHO PAYS FOR THE URGENT DELIVERIES?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide33">I HAVE NOT RECEIVED THE HANDBAG FOR THE DAY MY RENTAL PERIOD STARTS FROM. WHY AND WHAT NOW?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide34">WHAT IF MY RENTAL ENDS ON A SUNDAY OR A HOLIDAY?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide35">CAN YOU DELIVER THE PACKAGE TO A DIFFERENT ADDRESS TO THE ONE I GAVE YOU ORIGINALLY?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide36">HOW MUCH DOES SHIPPING COST?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide37">DO YOU SHIP TO&nbsp;P.O. BOXES&nbsp;OR INTERNATIONAL ADDRESSES?</div>\r\n<h3>REFUNDS, CANCELLATION AND EXCHANGES</h3>\r\n<div class="question show_hide38">WHEN WILL I RECEIVE MY REFUND?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide39">HOW CAN I CANCEL MY ORDER?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide40">HOW CAN I (EX)CHANGE MY ORDER?</div>\r\n<h3>DAMAGES</h3>\r\n<div class="question show_hide41">I&nbsp;DAMAGED THE BAG. WHAT HAPPENS NOW?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide42">I LOST THE HANDBAG I BORROWED FROM YOU. WHAT HAPPENS NOW?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide43">THE HANDBAG I RENTED FROM YOU HAS BEEN STOLEN. WHAT HAPPENS NOW?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide44">DO YOU OFFER INSURANCE?</div>\r\n<h3>REWARDS AND LOYALTY</h3>\r\n<div class="question show_hide45">WHY IS MY&nbsp;REWARDS NOT WORKING?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide46">CAN I MAKE A CHANGE TO MY ORDER&nbsp;ONCE IT HAS BEEN PLACED?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide47">CAN I PURCHASE A HANDBAG?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide48">HOW DO I EARN CREDITS&nbsp;ON&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG WEBSITE?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide49">CAN I TURN CREDITS INTO CASH?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide50">HOW LONG DO THE CREDITS&nbsp;STAY ON MY ACCOUNT&nbsp;FOR MY USE?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide51">I DO NOT HAVE ENOUGH CREDITS TO REDEEM TOWARDS MY NEXT RENTAL&nbsp;AND MY EXISTING CREDITS WILL EXPIRE SOON. WHAT DO I DO?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide52">WHY SHOULD I EARN CREDITS FROM RENT-A-BAG?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide53">HOW CAN I REDEEM MY CREDITS?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide54">DO I EARN CREDITS FROM A BUY TO RENT PURCHASE?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide55">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide56">HOW CAN I MONITOR&nbsp;MY CREDITS?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide57">DO I RECEIVE ANY CREDITS&nbsp;IF I RETURN A RENTED HANDBAG EARLIER?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide58">HOW ELSE CAN I EARN EXTRA POINTS?</div>\r\n<h3>MY ACCOUNT</h3>\r\n<div class="question show_hide59">WHAT IS&nbsp;MY ACCOUNT?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide60">WHY SHOULD I REGISTER?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide61">HOW DO I REGISTER?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide62">WHY DO I NEED TO SUPPLY MY ID TO YOU?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide63">HOW DO I CHANGE MY PERSONAL DETAILS IN MY ACCOUNT?</div>\r\n<h3>PAYMENT</h3>\r\n<div class="question show_hide64">HOW CAN I PAY FOR MY ORDERS?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide65">I WAS CHARGED TWICE. WHY IS THAT?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide66">HOW MANY PAYMENTS ARE YOU TAKING WHEN I AM MAKING A RESERVATION FOR A HANDBAG?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide67">WHEN AM I CHARGED FOR A RENTAL?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide68">WHAT DOES PREPAYMENT OR PRE-AUTHORISATION MEAN?</div>\r\n<div class="question show_hide69">WHY DO I NEED A CREDIT CHECK?</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '2016-03-18 12:28:38', '2016-03-18 12:29:17', 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(10, 'Return policy', 'one_column', NULL, NULL, 'return-policy', NULL, '<header class="entry-header">\r\n<h1 class="entry-title">RETURN POLICY</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n<div class="entry-content">\r\n<div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid">\r\n<div class="row-container">\r\n<div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12">\r\n<div class="wpb_wrapper">\r\n<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">\r\n<div class="wpb_wrapper">\r\n<div class="justify">\r\n<h3>RENT A BAG</h3>\r\n<p>We understand that circumstances can change and we help you to be flexible with your needs. Should you need to exchange or refund an item please email us on bag@rent-a-bag.club.</p>\r\n<p>CANCELLATIONS</p>\r\n<p>If you change your mind 7 or more days before your rental starts you can cancel your order free of charge, you will get a full refund.</p>\r\n<p>Should you cancel your order 7 or less days before your rental start day, you will receive a full credit minus &pound;20, which is our administrative charge. The credit is valid for the next 6 months from its issue date.</p>\r\n<p>Cancellations are accepted within 48 hours prior the dispatch with no refunds being allowed.</p>\r\n<p>EXCHANGES</p>\r\n<p>Should you wish to exchange the order for another item, please make a new order and follow the cancellation steps for the order which has already been placed and which requires an exchange.</p>\r\n<p>Our refunds are processed within 3-5 working days back to the account you have used to pay for the item.</p>\r\n<p>RETURNS AND REFUNDS</p>\r\n<p>If you received your order and you would like to return it, please notify us by email customersupport@rent-a-bag.club and post the item back to us in the packaging provided.</p>\r\n<p>The item must have the Authenticity Tag still attached and should be shipped within the next 1 (one) working day. Once we receive the item, we inspect it and once it cleared from all the damages, etc we will issue you a full credit minus &pound;20 and less shipping costs occurred. The credit is valid for 6 (six) months from its issue date. You will have to provide a reasonable reason why you are returning the bag.</p>\r\n<p>Items must be unused and in the original condition in which they were sent. Items without authenticity tags will not be accepted for refunds.</p>\r\n<h3>BUY TO RENT</h3>\r\n<p>If you choose a bag and pay for it, you have a cool down period of 14 days to cancel your order.</p>\r\n<p>Please notify us by email.</p>\r\n<p>Our refunds are processed within 3-5 working days back to the account you have used to pay for the item.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '2016-03-18 12:48:01', '2016-03-18 12:48:01', 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11, 'RENT-A-BAG TERMS AND CONDITIONS ', 'one_column', NULL, NULL, 'rent-a-bag_terms_and_conditions', 'RENT-A-BAG TERMS AND CONDITIONS ', '<ol>\r\n<li>ACCEPTANCE OF TERMS OF USE</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>The following Terms of Service (&ldquo;Terms&rdquo;) between you (&ldquo;you&rdquo; or &ldquo;your&rdquo;) and RENT-A-BAG (&ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;our,&rdquo; &ldquo;us,&rdquo; or &ldquo;Rent-a-Bag.club&rdquo;) describes the terms and conditions on which you may access and use the Rent-a-bag website located at www.rent-a-bag.club (the &ldquo;Site&rdquo;), the RENT-A-BAG mobile app (the &ldquo;App&rdquo;) and related services including RENT-A-BAG&rsquo;s product rental and sale services (together with the Site, the App, and the RENT-A-BAG Content, as defined below, the &ldquo;Services&rdquo;). These Terms also apply to online in-store rentals and sales, which are part of the Services. By accessing or using any of the Services, you acknowledge that you have read, understood and agreed to be bound by these Terms.</p>\r\n<p>These terms and conditions, regarding&nbsp;the Privacy Policy, are a legal agreement between the natural or legal person and RENT-A-BAG, a trading name of a company ROONDO Ltd, a company registered in England and Wales under registration number 08924717, address Churchill House, 137-139 Brent Street, London, NW4 4DJ, United Kingdom, establishing terms and conditions under which you will submit information to, and hire bags and receive related services from, RENT-A-BAG via our website at&nbsp;<a href="{{config path="web/secure/base_url"}}">www.rent-a-bag.club</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG IS A UNITED KINGDOM BASED COMPANY THAT ONLY SHIPS BAGS FOR RENT WITHIN THE UNITED KINGDOM AND NORTHERN IRELAND. RENT-A-BAG DOES NOT SHIP BAGS TO RENT OUTSIDE THE THE UNITED KINGDOM AND NORTHERN IRELAND.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;This Agreement contains all the terms and conditions governing your rental from RENT-A-BAG. No other terms or conditions shall have any force or effect. In case of inconsistency between the rules contained in this document and any of the documents referred here, rule the terms and conditions set forth in this document.</p>\r\n<ol start="2">\r\n<li>OBTAINING AN ACCOUNT AND BECOMING A MEMBER</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Before you can begin use of the Service, you must register through the Site to obtain an account. By registering as a member through the Site you give us permission to obtain credit information from consumer credit-reporting agencies. Typically this is done when requesting a "Credit Check Required" item however we reserve the right to perform this at any time you request a rental item. You must be 18 years of age or older to register as a member and use the Service. You agree to provide true, accurate, current and complete information about yourself as prompted by the Site''s registration form (such information being the "Registration Data"), and you agree to maintain and promptly update the Registration Data to keep it true, accurate, current and complete. If you provide any information that is untrue, inaccurate, not current or incomplete, or we have any reasonable grounds to suspect that such information is untrue, inaccurate, not current or incomplete, we may suspend or terminate your Account and refuse to offer you any and all current or future use of the Service and the Site. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your Account and password and for restricting access to your computer. You are solely responsible for any activity related to your Account. If you suspect any unauthorised use of your Account, notify us immediately. In order to provide you with ease of access to your Account, we may place a cookie (a small text file) on the computers from which you access the Site. When you revisit the Site, this cookie will enable us to recognise you as the Account holder and allow you to more easily access your Account.</p>\r\n<p>2.1. Thus, before using this RENT-A-BAG Service the Customer must:</p>\r\n<p>2.1.1&nbsp;Be legally capable of entering into binding contracts;</p>\r\n<p>2.1.2. At least eighty (18) years old;</p>\r\n<p>2.1.3. You must have a valid credit or debit card with a bank or other provider acceptable to RENT-A-BAG and you must have provided us with the details of such card. The card must be registered to your home address.</p>\r\n<p>2.1.4. Proof of residency in the form of a utility bill, bank statement, driving license, and/or passport i could be necessary.</p>\r\n<p>2.1.5. PROOF OF ID COULD BE REQUIRED WHEN MAKING YOUR FIRST RENTAL AND A CREDIT CHECK COULD BE PERFORMED. Please ensure that you have the following proofs when joining:</p>\r\n<p>2.1.6. Photocopy of a Bank Statement within the last three months, photo ID Drivers License or UK Passport, photocopy of bank card details both front and back of the card &amp; a utility bill in your name COULD BE REQUIRED WHEN MAKING YOUR FIRST RENTAL.</p>\r\n<p>2.1.7. The proofs need to be visual and as clear as possible.</p>\r\n<p>2.1.8. RENT-A-BAG requires all these details for our records. Once obtained and approved RENT-A-BAG makes sure to keep all your data confidential.</p>\r\n<p>2.2. RENT-A-BAG has taken great care to ensure that the items on its website are presented as accurately as possible. However, colour clarity will depend upon customers&rsquo; own personal monitors and RENT-A-BAG therefore cannot guarantee that the colour of the actual Item is absolutely accurate. Customers should read through these terms before placing an order.</p>\r\n<ol start="3">\r\n<li>MODIFICATION TO TERMS OF USE</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>We reserve the right to modify these Terms and Conditions at any time and in any manner at our sole discretion. Notice of any modification of these Terms and Conditions will be posted in this section of the Site, and any such modifications will be effective upon the posting of such notice. Your continued use of the Site constitutes your binding acceptance of such modifications. Please check this section of the Site before using the Site to determine whether a change has been made to these Terms and Conditions. If you do not agree to any changes in the Terms of Use as they may occur, please arrange to terminate your registration with the Site immediately (a) by notifying RENT-A-BAG of your unwillingness to accept the changes to the Terms and Conditions and Service by emailing info@rent-a-bag.com or calling us at +44 (0) 20 3290 9498; and (b) by discontinuing your use of the Service and the Site. You agree that we shall not be liable to you or to any third party for any modification of the Terms and Conditions.</p>\r\n<ol start="4">\r\n<li>REGISTRATION</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Access the customer registration&nbsp;page and provide only true, accurate, complete and updated information. You must enter your email address or contact. You can change the data in your account, at any time.</p>\r\n<p>You assume sole and exclusive responsibility for the confidentiality and security of your account information, especially your password.</p>\r\n<ol start="5">\r\n<li>THE RENT-A-BAG SERVICE</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>5.1. The Service allows customers to access the Site and purchase or borrow products from RENT-A-BAG in accordance with these Terms of Use. The customer can choose products to borrow from our extensive on-line selection, and have them shipped to the customer''s address. This is done with a return date. We reserve the right to limit the number of items that a member may borrow at any time. The currently available borrowing options and rates, are outlined in detail on the Site. Also, the current shipping policies governing the delivery and return of products are detailed on the Site. Delivery time for products you have selected to borrow may vary based upon a) inventory availability, b) your delivery address, c) when you place an order, and d) other circumstances impacting delivery. Accordingly, RENT-A-BAG makes no guarantees as to actual delivery time. The risk of loss for items shipped passes to you upon our delivery to the carrier. We will send you an email letting you know when your product is shipped.</p>\r\n<p>5.2. If a product is returned in a damaged or dirty condition that exceeds normal wear and tear, as determined by RENT-A-BAG in its sole discretion, you agree that RENT-A-BAG may invoice you for the full cost of replacing such product as well as charge you the full amount of any lost earnings or incurred costs resulting from the damage. The product replacement fee will vary depending on the specifics of each bag and its amount is to the full discretion of RENT-A-BAG.</p>\r\n<p>5.3. Under no circumstances are customers to attempt to clean any products themselves by any means (dry cleaned or otherwise). If done so, RENT-A-BAG reserves the right to invoice for part or full replacement value of the items and charge you the full amount of any potential lost earnings or incurred costs regardless of whether any damage has been caused.</p>\r\n<p>5.4. Any discounts, vouchers or offers made available on the site or through third party channels which are redeemable on the RENT-A-BAG site are subject to change without notice.</p>\r\n<ol start="6">\r\n<li>BILLING</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>6.1. When you rent or buy a bag you will be required to provide RENT-A-BAG with accurate, complete and current information of a valid credit or debit card of which you re the lawful owner (as prompted by the site) and that by default you are authorised to use. By signing up for the Service, you authorise RENT-A-BAG or its agent to bill your credit or debit card the applicable fees, per-item or borrowing fees, shipping charges, any and all applicable taxes, and any other charges you may incur in connection with your use of the Service. The applicable fees will be charged to your credit or debit card on the date your purchase is made. If the bag you borrowed is not returned on the due return date agreed when the purchase was made, RENT-A-BAG will charge your credit or debit card in according with the rate set for that bag as stated on the site, until a return shipment has been booked by the customer and RENT-A-BAG are notified by the courier company.</p>\r\n<p>6.2. If RENT-A-BAG does not receive payment from your credit card provider or if your credit card expires or is rejected, you agree to pay all amounts due upon demand. RENT-A-BAG reserves the right to take all steps necessary to collect amounts due from you, including but not limited to using third party collection agencies. RENT-A-BAG reserves the right to correct any errors or mistakes that it makes even if it has already requested or received payment.</p>\r\n<p>6.3. You are solely responsible for any and all fees charged to your credit card by the issuer, bank, or financial institution including, but not limited to, overdraft, insufficient funds, and over the credit limit fees. You agree to notify us about any billing problems or discrepancies within 90 days after they first appear on your account statement. If you do not bring them to our attention within 90 days, you agree that you waive your right to dispute such problems or discrepancies.</p>\r\n<p>6.4. We may modify the price, content, or nature of the Service at any time. We may provide notice of any such changes by email, notice to you upon log-in, or by publishing them on the Site.</p>\r\n<ol start="7">\r\n<li>PRODUCTS</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>7.1. All orders are subject to availability. In the absence or difficulty to supply,&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;reserves the right to inform you of products with equal style, quality and price. You must confirm the new order.&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;will refund you for already paid products.</p>\r\n<p>7.2. RENT-A-BAG product catalogue is liable to change at any time. The characteristics of the products are as described at the time of the hire. All images found on the site are illustrative. Descriptions of the products do not assure conformity or suitability of a product for an exact purpose, neither must be free of any unintentionally errors.</p>\r\n<p>7.3. The products listed in the catalogue are available for delivery to the United Kingdom and Northern Ireland.</p>\r\n<p>7.4. The product pricing is as displayed at the time of the hire. The final price may vary according to the country of delivery, shipping costs and legal taxes.</p>\r\n<ol start="8">\r\n<li>USE OF PRODUCTS</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>You agree to treat the Products with great care, as if it was borrowed from your close friend. You are responsible for loss, destruction or damage to the Products due to theft, mysterious disappearance, fire, major stains or any other cause, other than normal wear and tear. If you return a Product that is damaged beyond normal wear and tear, then you agree that we shall charge you, and you shall pay, for the price for repairing or replacing the Product, as determined in our discretion, up to the Retail Value for the Product.</p>\r\n<ol start="9">\r\n<li>AVAILABILITY AND DELIVERY</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>If the item&nbsp;ordered is not available or are not delivered within the requested time,&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;will inform you and suggest an alternative style in the same quality and price range. In this case, the customer can accept the suggestion, make a new request, or cancel the previous one. If the order is canceled the customer will receive full refund as per our refund and exchange policy (to its account or chosen payment method).</p>\r\n<ol start="10">\r\n<li>ORDER</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>10.1. To proceed with any order you must complete our online form and follow the rent process available on the page.</p>\r\n<p>10.2. After you place the order, you will receive a confirmation email. However, this may not mean your order is accepted. Only the second email, with expected date of dispatch, product description and price, will ultimately confirm the order.</p>\r\n<p>10.3. Each customer can have only TWO (2) bags for rent in total in possession at each time and cannot make a new order, until the previous order has been returned making it only two bags in possession at one particular time. The customer cannot make alterations for the bags, or he will have to pay the full retail price as quoted on Rent-a-bag website from the altered bag.</p>\r\n<p>10.4. We recommend to place orders at least four weeks in advance, to ensure the availability of the chosen bag at the desired date. However, the customer is able to order up to 2 (two) business days before the required date. Nevertheless,&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;does not ensure that the bag will be available.</p>\r\n<ol start="11">\r\n<li>CONTRACT FORMATION</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>The rental agreement between&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;and the customer will only be formed when the customer received the order confirmation email, whether or not&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;has already received the payment.</p>\r\n<ol start="12">\r\n<li>SERVICE CONDITIONS</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>12.1. RENT-A-BAG&rsquo;s&nbsp;rental service is limited to a maximum of 2 (two) bags per order and a total of 2 (two) items at any given time.</p>\r\n<p>12.2. Rented products are made available for a period of minimum 1 (one) week (7 (seven) days) with a maximum of 2 (two) weeks (14 (fourteen) days). If rental time period is exceeded, the customer will be subject to penalties. However, should a customer wishes to extend the rental period, s/he can do so by informing RENT-A-BAG as soon as possible. RENT-A-BAG reserves the right not to prolong the rental period. The extension of the rental period complies with the whole process of rental order of an item.</p>\r\n<p>12.3. You acknowledge and agree that we may place limits on the rental or purchase of products, including but not limited to restricting orders placed under a single customer account, payment card or billing or shipping address. We reserve the right to limit, cancel or prohibit any rentals or sales of products for any reason, including but not limited to availability concerns.</p>\r\n<ol start="13">\r\n<li>PRICES</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>13.1. Prices (with VAT) include delivery and shipping costs. They are per unit and may vary depending on the type, model and label. The price of the required bag can be seen on a bag detail page. RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;may change prices with no impact on confirmed orders.</p>\r\n<p>13.2. You are responsible for loss, destruction or damage to the bag, such as theft, fire, major stains or any other cause, other than minor damages. Please understand that if the bag is returned with any kind of these irreversible damages, you must pay the full retail price according to our price list.</p>\r\n<p>13.3. Under no circumstances are customers to attempt to clean any bags themselves.</p>\r\n<ol start="14">\r\n<li>PAYMENT TERMS</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>14.1. The order will only be charged when you make your reservation. The invoice will be emailed during the dispatch of the order.</p>\r\n<p>14.2. RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;will verify the address and credibility of the order.</p>\r\n<p>14.3. We are not responsible for any fees or charges that your bank or credit card issuer may apply. If your credit or debit card issuer reverses a charge to your credit card, we may bill your account directly and seek payment by another method including a mailed statement.</p>\r\n<ol start="15">\r\n<li>REWARD-LOYALTY POINTS</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Reward points are accrued by: 1 Reward point for every GBP10 (ten) spent on all Rentals. In addition, we also credit your account with 10% off from a rented bag off the rent value of the handbag in case of early return of the bag. Each10% off converts to 1 (one) Loyalty Reward. These can be used towards Rental of any in-stock item for rent. Reward points cannot be used towards purchases, expedited shipping, return shipping of a purchased item, or renewal rental fees. Reward points do not have cash value, cannot be exchanged for store credit, and cannot be transferred to another account. Your reward points will expire after 6 months if there are no transactions in your account. The 6 month period begins with the most recent transaction in your account. All reward points will be forfeited when an account is terminated for any reason or if an account goes into default or outstanding status, owing any fees for current rental items. When you redeem your loyalty points, you pay for shipping of the handbag to your address and back to us.</p>\r\n<ol start="16">\r\n<li>GIFT CARDS</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>We offer Gift Cards that can vary in amount and be applied toward any RENT-A-BAG service or item. In purchasing a Gift Card, you authorise us to charge your credit card. Gift Cards are subject to the additional terms and conditions set forth on the "Gift Subscriptions" page.</p>\r\n<ol start="17">\r\n<li>DEPOSIT</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>In conformity with the obligations under these&nbsp;Terms of Use,&nbsp;and as a guarantee, RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;will be authorised to charge your credit card in the amount equal to the retail price of the items ordered.</p>\r\n<ol start="18">\r\n<li>INSURANCE</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>18.1. We strongly advise the customer to hold valid home contents insurance and to notify your insurers before renting a bag.</p>\r\n<p>18.2. Risk in the Hire Goods and any Products will pass immediately to the Customer when they leave the physical possession or the control of the Supplier.</p>\r\n<p>18.2.1. Risk in the Hire Goods will not pass back to the Supplier from the Customer until the rented bags are back in the physical possession of RENT-A-BAG. This shall apply even if RENT-A-BAG has agreed to cease charging the Rental;</p>\r\n<p>18.2.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;Title in the Hire Goods remains at all times with the Supplier. The Customer has no right, title or interest in the Hire Goods except that they are hired to the Customer;</p>\r\n<p>18.2.4.&nbsp;Title in any Products remains with the Supplier until all monies payable to the Supplier by the Customer for the Products have been paid in full;</p>\r\n<p>18.2.5.&nbsp;The Customer must not deal with the title or any interest in the Hire Goods. This includes but is not limited to selling, assigning, mortgaging, pledging, charging, securing, hiring, exerting a lien and/or lending;</p>\r\n<p>18.2.6.&nbsp;The Supplier may require the Customer to insure the Hire Goods on such reasonable terms and for such reasonable risks as the Supplier may specify. The proceeds of any such insurance shall be held by the Customer in trust for the Supplier and be paid to the Supplier on demand. The Customer must not compromise any claim in respect of the Hire Goods and/or any associated insurance without the Supplier&rsquo;s written consent;</p>\r\n<p>18.6.&nbsp;In any event, the Supplier strongly recommends that the Customer insures the Hire Goods to the full cost of replacement of the Hire Goods. If the Supplier has an existing household insurance policy that will cover any loss or damage to the Hire Goods, the Customer should ensure that their insurance provider is notified before the Hire Goods are hired.</p>\r\n<ol start="19">\r\n<li>DELIVERY AND SHIPPING</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>19.1. After payment confirmation and availability of the required bag, the dispatch of the order will be completed up to forty-eight (48) hours before the start rental date you selected. The dispatch of the order includes a pre-paid label with no extra charge. The prepaid label and delivery package should be kept and used to return the bag.</p>\r\n<p>19.2. Payment detail, such as time, cost and conditions of delivery depend on the type of payment you selected.</p>\r\n<p>19.3. If you are not at the address of delivery on the requested day, you will have to contact&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;to arrange a new delivery date. That may increase additional shipping costs. If you do not contact&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;within forty-eight (48) hours from the attempted delivery,&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;will consider your order cancelled. You will be charged of the total service value without any kind of refund.</p>\r\n<ol start="20">\r\n<li>RETURN</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>20.1. RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;will send you a return form along with the items chosen by you for rent, which you must fill in at the order return. You must check the various points listed in the return form and ensure that you have placed the bags in the prepaid and self addressed delivery package.</p>\r\n<p>20.2. The items returned should be:</p>\r\n<p>- In perfect condition without any irreversible damages;</p>\r\n<p>- In the same condition they were delivered with the respective boxes/dust-bags or other goods.</p>\r\n<p>20.3. You are the sole responsible for any damage the products can suffer. In accordance to that, you have the legal obligation to make a prudent use of the products, while they are in your possession.</p>\r\n<p>If you fail to this obligation, we have the right of action against you for compensation.</p>\r\n<p>Please do know that we do not give refunds if a bag is returned to us earlier.</p>\r\n<ol start="21">\r\n<li>LOST RETURN PACKAGING</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>If you lose the Return Packaging, you will be responsible for returning the item at your own expense by the expected return date, and providing RENT-A-BAG with a tracking number.</p>\r\n<ol start="22">\r\n<li>PENALTIES AND LATE FEES</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>22.1. In case you fail to return the products on time or not at all, you shall immediately inform</p>\r\n<p>RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;by email customersupport@rent-a-bag.club. If such happens, you are liable to pay the following penalties:</p>\r\n<p>22.2. RENT-A-BAG reserves the right to charge &pound;50 for the first 24 hours after the established return date.</p>\r\n<p>If after 24 hours the delay still occurs, you will be charged an amount of 100% of the maximum RENT-A-BAG rental period price (which is 14 (fourteen) days of the ordered bag on the card provided to pay for this rental or to any other payment card included in your account information that you have provided to RENT-A-BAG;</p>\r\n<p>- If after the first five (5) days of the established return date the products have not been returned, legal consequences will be handled. Subsequently, you will be required to pay the full retail price of all items ordered and RENT-A-BAG reserves the right to keep full deposit paid for the items;</p>\r\n<p>- If the products are not delivered one time on the settled date, your account may be suspended or canceled.</p>\r\n<p>- If the products are returned with irreversible damage, you will have to pay the product&acute;s full retail price.</p>\r\n<ol start="23">\r\n<li>CANCELLATIONS: COSTS AND REFUNDS</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>If you choose to cancel the order, you may return a rented product and obtain a refund. You must deposit the item for return within 1 (one) working day from when you receive the item and provide us a valid reason. RENT-A-BAG reserves the right to charge the full rental fee. Please contact customersupport@rent-a-bag.club if you need to return the item. RENT-A-BAG processes the refunds within 3-5 working days after we receive the time and clear of all the damages. RENT-A-BAG however reserves the right to process a refund within 14 days of a request for a refund unless the order is being disputed.</p>\r\n<p>All items&rsquo; tags MUST remain intact and with the Authenticity Tags on. If you fail to fulfil agreed upon terms, your debit/credit card will be charged for the full, non-discounted fees and charges for the entire period you booked the bag for.</p>\r\n<p>If you wish to cancel your order BEFORE it is delivered, please let us know as soon as you can by contacting customer service on&nbsp;<a href="mailto:customersupport@rent-a-bag.club">customersupport@rent-a-bag.club</a>&nbsp;and we will be happy to take care of it for you as per our cancellation, exchanges, returns and refunds policy.</p>\r\n<ol start="24">\r\n<li>CANCELLATIONS, EXCHANGES, RETURNS AND REFUND</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>24.1. CANCELLATIONS</p>\r\n<p>If you change your mind 7 or more days before your rental starts you can cancel your order free of charge, you will get a full refund.</p>\r\n<p>Should you cancel your order 7 or less days before your rental start day, you will receive a full credit minus &pound;20, which is our administrative charge. The credit is valid for the next 6 months from its issue date.</p>\r\n<p>Cancellations are accepted within 48 hours prior the dispatch with no refunds being allowed.</p>\r\n<p>24.2. EXCHANGES</p>\r\n<p>Should you wish to exchange your order for another item, please make a new order and follow the cancellation steps for the order which has already been placed and which requires an exchange.</p>\r\n<p>Our refunds are processed within 3-5 working days.</p>\r\n<p>24.3. RETURNS AND REFUNDS</p>\r\n<p>If you received your order and you would like to return it, please notify us by email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:customersupport@rent-a-bag.club">customersupport@rent-a-bag.club</a>&nbsp;and post the item back to us in the packaging provided.</p>\r\n<p>The item must have the Authenticity Tag still attached and should be shipped within the next 1 (one) working day. Once we receive the item, we inspect it and once it cleared from all the damages, etc we will issue you a full credit minus &pound;20 and less shipping costs occurred. The credit is valid for 6 (six) months from its issue date. You will have to provide a reasonable reason why you are returning the bag.</p>\r\n<p>Items must be unused and in the original condition in which they were sent. Items without authenticity tags will not be accepted for refunds.</p>\r\n<ol start="25">\r\n<li>PRICES</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Prices are valid until 6pm of the following business day of the order&rsquo;s submission.&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;may change those prices from that date on.</p>\r\n<p>METHODS AND TERMS OF PAYMENT</p>\r\n<p>The RENT-A-BAG&rsquo;s available payment method is Credit or Debit Card and alternative payment methods like PayPal. We are constantly looking at the best suited to our customers payment methods and thus can be added without notifications to our website.</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>BAGS BUY TO RENT</li>\r\n</ol><ol>\r\n<li>Should you purchase your handbag for the 6 months option, RENT-A-BAG pays you off the full price within 6 months, 10% on top and the handbag;</li>\r\n<li>Should you purchase your handbag for the 12 months option, RENT-A-BAG pays you off the full price within 12 months, 12% on top and the handbag;</li>\r\n<li>You can monitor your bag&rsquo;s performance from &lsquo;My Account&rsquo;;</li>\r\n<li>We ship you your handbag at the end of your chosen &lsquo;investment&rsquo; option. You pay for the shipment.</li>\r\n<li>Cancellations, refunds, exchanges of the handbags are not permitted.</li>\r\n</ol><ol>\r\n<li>YOUR RIGHTS AS A BAG OWNER</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>i.. Once the bag is purchased and the money is cleared in our bank account you are a sole owner of the bag;</p>\r\n<p>ii.. We reserve the right to advertise the purchased handbag on our website as a handbag for rent immediately once the purchase is complete and you consent for the bag to be rented out to our customers;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Cancellation is not possible once a first reservation is being made on your handbag. We accept cancelation of your purchase within 30 days should there is no reservation being made within this time frame and your reason for cancellation is that the product is of unsatisfactory quality, unfit for purpose or not as described;</li>\r\n<li>We reserve the right to keep you bag until your chosen plan ends;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>vii.. Refund is not possible once a first rental reservation is being made on the handbag;</p>\r\n<p>viii. Exchange is not possible once a first reservation is being made on the handbag;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>All handbags purchased for BUY-TO-RENT plan are new;</li>\r\n<li>Rental process of your handbag is fully covered by the rental process of these terms and conditions;</li>\r\n<li>RENT-A-BAG has a duty to make timely payments to the handbag&rsquo;s owner account every two months; payments are made to the account of the handbag owner&rsquo;s choice;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>xii. RENT-A-BAG does not limit on number of handbags a customer wishes to buy for rent;</p>\r\n<p>xiii. RENT-A-BAG guarantees to take care of the handbag to maintain it in the &lsquo;like new&rsquo; condition;</p>\r\n<p>xiv. The rental process is the same as described for rent-a-bag.</p>\r\n<p>III. FINAL PROVISIONS</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHTS</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>You acknowledge that the site and all its contents, such as software, logo or symbols, are owned by&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;or have been duly licensed.</p>\r\n<p>You accept that intellectual property rights, that you must respect, protect the contents of this website.</p>\r\n<p>Rent-a-bag&nbsp;will manage the design, layout and all other information on the site.&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;may, at any time, update, modify or delete any content, services, features or options.</p>\r\n<p>You are not authorised to modify, change, copy, sell or use any content of the site without the consent of RENT-A-BAG.</p>\r\n<p>The items listed in the product catalogue belong to specific designers and&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;is neither accountable nor holds any rights over them. You must respect their rules of usage as well as the limitations.</p>\r\n<ol start="2">\r\n<li>PERSONAL DATA</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Your personal data will be processed taking into account the legal provisions in force and our privacy policy.</p>\r\n<p>To access the&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG services you must register with some personal information about yourself. Non-registered customers may also provide their personal data, in which case the present rules are also applied.</p>\r\n<p>When you access RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;services,&nbsp;you also will be required to provide valid credit or debit card information or other payment information.</p>\r\n<p>Your personal data will be processed and stored. RENT-A-BAG uses that information to manage the contractual relationship with you. If you authorise it, RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;also may use your information for marketing services, through communications that do not need your intervention.</p>\r\n<p>Under applicable law, you have the right to access, correct and update your personal data without any costs. Therefore, you must contact the entity responsible for processing the data to the address:&nbsp;Churchill House, 137-139 Brent Street, London, NW4 4DJ, United Kingdom.</p>\r\n<p>RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;adopted the appropriate security measures. However, RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;must not be held responsible of unauthorised use of your personal data by third parties.</p>\r\n<ol start="3">\r\n<li>LINKS</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>RENT-A-BAG may provide links to other entities. These entities are not owned, operated or controlled by&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG, so&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;is not responsible, for the content of these sites or the sites connected to them or therein, in any way.</p>\r\n<p>Establishing links does not imply any relations between&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;and the owner or manager of the web page to which the link refers. You are the sole responsible for using those links.</p>\r\n<ol start="4">\r\n<li>SAFETY</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>The&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG&nbsp;does not ensure that the site will work uninterruptedly.</p>\r\n<p>Rent-a-bag&nbsp;makes their best efforts to have an error free and continuously available site without dangerous elements to your computer. However, since&nbsp;RENT-A-BAG cannot fully control the Internet&rsquo;s flow of information, it cannot ensure that they do not contain any elements that may harm your computer.</p>\r\n<p>Rent-a-bag&nbsp;may, at any time and without prior notice, take steps to ensure the security and quality of the site, including restricting or limiting access.</p>\r\n<ol start="5">\r\n<li>BREACH OF CONTRACT</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>If you d